737
Western Pacific
AIRLINES
For your safety...
Government regulations require that a passenger seated in a designated exit seat
notify a crew member prior to departure if: You do not read, speak or understand
the language in which your flight crew delivered the pre-flight briefing.
Para su seguridad...
Los reglamentos del gobierno requieren que un pasajero sentado en un
asiento designado de salida de emergencia, le haga saber a un miembro de
la tripulación antes de la salida del vuelo si no puede leer, hablar o entender
el idioma en el que los miembros de la tripulación la dieron las instrucciones
previas al vuelo.
EXIT ROW SEATING REGULATIONS
To sit in an emergency exit seat, you must:
1. Read English well enough to understand the instructions for opening exits
and for other emergency procedures.
2. See well enough to read these instructions, see hand signals given by
crew members, and look outside for dangers such as smoke, fire or water
which would make the exit unusable.
You can wear eyeglasses or contact
lenses.
3. Hear well enough to understand English commands. You can use a hearing aid.
4. Speak well enough to give information in English to crew members or other
passengers during an emergency.
5. Have the strength, mobility, or dexterity to quickly open the exit and assist other
passengers through the exit and away from the plane.
Some window hatches
that must be lifted weigh as much as 65 pounds (the approximate weight of a 7
year old child).
6. Be at least 15 years old.
7. Have no other responsibilities, such as caring for a small child, that would distract
you from occupying an emergency exit row seat.
You must be willing and able to do all of these things by yourself and without
causing harm to yourself.
If you are unwilling or unable (due to a discernible
or nondiscernible condition) to accept the prescribed responsibilities, you
cannot occupy an emergency exit row seat.
If you are already seated there,
ask a crew member or customer service agent to assist you to another seat.
You do not have to explain why.
Please obey the "No Smoking" and "Fasten Seatbelt" signs
and all instructions given by your crew members.
FOR THE SAFETY OF FUTURE PASSENGERS
PLEASE DO NOT REMOVE THIS CARD FROM THE AIRCRAFT.
PARA LA SEGURIDAD DE PASAJEROS FUTUROS, POR FAVOR
NO RETIRE ESTA TARJETA DEL AVION.
